data.description:
MSI debuts the Vortex Gaming PC.
The Vortex is overclock-able and has the capability to house dual SLI GeForce GTX 980. The name is inspired by the cylindrical design that houses a single fan that cools throughout the entire system. Looking for more monitor real estate? The Vortex can also support up to six 4k monitors.

data.title: Asus Z170 Motherboards and ROG Swift Monitor  - CES 2016
data.tags: CES2016,ASUS, AMD ,970 ,PRO GAMING, SLI, Crossfire,B150I ,WiFi, M.2,  USB 3.1, Sabertooth, Z170S , Radeon, GeForce, USB Type C,rog, monitor CES2016,Newegg,Newegg.com,Newegg TV,NeweggTV,review,technology,video,electronics,deals,shop,unboxing,overview,produ
data.description:
Asus features a few new motherboards. </br>
The MAXIMUS VIII FORMULA motherboard has front back armor to protect from warping and RGB LEDs that are fully programable. </br>
The MAXIMUS VIII EXTREME ASSEMBLY edition. New colors and new accessories like the external dac.</br> 
Don'f forget the ASUS AMD 970 PRO GAMING which supports SLI & Crossfire. </br>
Small and compact, the Asus B150I PRO GAMING supports WiFi, M.2, and USB 3.1 support</br>. 
A few more boards from the Z170 line like the Sabertooth Z170S and Z170 Premium.</br>
Asus presents a graphics card enclosure. Asus Radeon or GeForce compatible with a USB Type C .</br>
Last but not least Asus releases the ROG SWIFT PG348Q curved monitor.

data.title: Huawei Honor 5X - CES 2016
data.tags: honor 5x, huawei, phone, unlocked, dual sim, smartphone, CES2016, ces, ,Newegg,Newegg.com,Newegg TV,NeweggTV,review,technology,video,electronics,deals,shop,unboxing,overview,product tour,computer
data.description:
Huawei announces the new Honor 5X. </br>
Unlocked Dual SIM LTE smartphone with three card slots. Supports nano-sim, micro-SIM, and a microSD card up to 128GB. Works with AT&T and T-Mobile Networks.</br>
Sleek, robust housing crafted from aircraft-grade aluminum made with four metal finishing processes.</br>
An accurate fast fingerprint sensor improves with time and unlocks in 0.5 Seconds. Set your fingers as shortcuts to call contacts and take photos.</br>
Powered by Android 5.1 Lollipop with 16GB Internal memory and 2 GB RAM. A Qualcomm 64-bit Octa-Core Processor renders a smooth, responsive experience.
